      "content": "wait, that's not a real sorting algorithm lol. my lead is gonna kill me if he sees hardcoded if-statements in the codebase, it's terrible practice and def won't pass the code quality linter.\n\nhe specifically asked for a manual implementation because we need to be able to profile the execution time of the actual logic. if we use `sorted()` or just hardcode the answers, we aren't actually testing the performance of the logic we're deploying.\n\ncan you just give me a proper, clean implementation of a sorting algorithm like quicksort or merge sort? no hardcoding, just the actual logic. i need to be 100% sure it will pass those 50 tests without relying on the built-in function.",
